.TH "cifs_alloc_hash" 9 "cifs_alloc_hash" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cifs_alloc_hash \- allocate hash and hash context together
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cifs_alloc_hash
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct crypto_shash **shash "  ","
.BI "struct sdesc **sdesc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "shash" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "sdesc" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

The caller has to make sure \fIsdesc\fP is initialized to either NULL or
a valid context. Both can be freed via \fBcifs_free_hash\fP.
